        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 23 at 9:14PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 913 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Richmond, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northeastern Macomb
and central St. Clair Counties, including the following locations...
Columbus, Rattle Run, New Haven, Smiths Creek, and Adair.
</description>
